  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "BackgroundWhen it comes to models for solving NLP tasks, many people may think of long short-term memory (LSTM) and other recurrent neural networks (RNNs).",
    "But at present, LSTM is becoming less popular in the field of NLP because the parallel computing power of the LSTM model is poor.",
    "In addition to that, the transformer model [1] proposed by Google in 2017 has a stronger ability to extract features.",
    "In the Stanford Reading Comprehension Dataset (SQuAD2.0) list, the machine's performance has exceeded human performance, which is largely due to the proposal of the pre-training model BERT which is built based on the encoder of the transformer model.",
    "In this paper, we review and compare the different transformer models which are the BERT model, the XLNet model, the RoBERTa model, the GPT2 model, and the ALBERT model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In addition to that, the transformer model [1] proposed by Google in 2017 has a stronger ability to extract features."
  ]
}